## If in case git pull command not appears in localchanges in server in superputty ##
   use... git stash save "Stashing local changes before pull"

## using ansible.builtin.unarchive module in playbook ##
    using unarchive module for at a time ex: cart application download and extract at a time ##

## using loop module in playbook ##
    - name: install python
    ansible.builtin.yum:
      name: "{{item}}"
      state: installed
    loop:
    - python36
    - gcc
    - python3-devel
 one by one execute ex python36,gcc,python-deve1.

  ## using shell module in playbook ##
  for ex: ansible.builtin.shell: "curl -sL https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_lts.x | bash"
   using double codes is must in shell module ... "" .....
   
              
